14:28.367 --> 14:30.368
That was some weak tea, dude.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.830
Some people might say it was romantic.

14:34.248 --> 14:35.540
Yeah, no.

14:36.917 --> 14:39.878
But yet, here you two are still together.

14:40.546 --> 14:43.006
Even after you and l
had our crazy naked night.

14:43.173 --> 14:44.549
PENNY: That's enough.
LEONARD: Okay.

14:44.717 --> 14:45.884
I'm just saying...

14:46.051 --> 14:48.011
...that after all you've been through...

14:48.178 --> 14:52.348
...you get to look into each other's eyes
and say I love you.

14:52.766 --> 14:54.225
And that's beautiful.

14:57.730 --> 15:00.231
Actually, to this day
she's never really said it.

15:01.567 --> 15:03.735
Oh, Penny, that's ridiculous!

15:04.945 --> 15:07.530
You know you love him.
Look him in the eyes and say it.

15:07.698 --> 15:10.366
-Raj.
-You know you want to say it. Say it.

15:11.243 --> 15:13.244
Say you love him.

15:15.247 --> 15:16.706
Say it!

15:22.046 --> 15:23.796
I really thought she would say it.

15:31.805 --> 15:35.058
Have l ever told you
you're like a sexy praying mantis?

15:37.478 --> 15:39.938
Every time you drink alcohol.

15:40.773 --> 15:43.483
You know, what's wonderful
about the praying mantis...

15:44.068 --> 15:46.444
...they devour their mate.

15:47.321 --> 15:48.446
Your point being?

15:55.996 --> 15:57.997
Dessert is served.

15:59.208 --> 16:01.584
I just had cobbler.

16:02.836 --> 16:04.420
You know what?

16:04.922 --> 16:06.422
I'm done with this.

16:07.967 --> 16:10.510
-But where are you going?
-I'm leaving.

16:10.761 --> 16:13.429
You can't leave, I need you.

16:16.767 --> 16:19.352
-You do?
-Yes.

16:19.728 --> 16:21.437
You're my ride.

16:23.774 --> 16:25.066
Sheldon...

16:25.234 --> 16:28.069
...you either say something meaningful
and from the heart...

16:28.237 --> 16:29.654
...or you and l are done.

16:31.407 --> 16:32.740
All right.

16:34.702 --> 16:36.411
Please.

16:37.538 --> 16:38.746
[SHELDON CLEARS THROAT]

16:40.207 --> 16:41.791
Amy...

16:43.002 --> 16:45.003
...when l look in your eyes...

16:45.212 --> 16:47.505
...and you're looking back in mine...

16:47.673 --> 16:49.424
...everything feels...

16:49.591 --> 16:51.467
...not quite normal...

16:51.677 --> 16:53.511
...because l feel...

16:53.929 --> 16:57.265
...stronger and weaker at the same time.

16:57.433 --> 16:59.934
I feel excited...

17:00.102 --> 17:03.187
...and at the same time, terrified.

17:04.356 --> 17:05.606
The truth is...

17:05.858 --> 17:08.985
...I don't know what I feel...

17:09.153 --> 17:12.280
...except l know what kind of man
I want to be.

17:14.283 --> 17:15.992
Sheldon.

17:16.535 --> 17:17.785
That was beautiful.

17:17.953 --> 17:21.789
I should hope so,
that's from the first Spider-Man movie.

17:26.462 --> 17:28.004
I'll take it.

17:29.882 --> 17:33.384
Good.
Now, l assume we're splitting the check?

17:37.973 --> 17:40.183
-Hey, Stuart.
-Oh, hey.

17:40.476 --> 17:42.143
I was actually just about to close.

17:42.311 --> 17:44.562
-Oh, I'm sorry, l'll leave.
-No, no, it's okay.

17:44.772 --> 17:46.230
-Hang out.
-You sure?

17:46.398 --> 17:48.649
Yeah, you're my first customer today.

17:49.485 --> 17:50.818
All right, great.

17:50.986 --> 17:53.738
I'm, uh, having a nightcap,
you wanna join me?

17:54.156 --> 17:57.492
